newsitem.title: TAIWAN: Taiwan interbank rate ends down, seen stable.
newsitem.headline: Taiwan interbank rate ends down, seen stable.

text.p: Taiwan's overnight interbank rate closed slightly softer on Monday and dealers expected the rate to stabilise around five percent, a level central bank governor Sheu Yuan-dong said he desired.
The interbank rate finished at 4.975 percent against Saturday's 4.982 close, with 30-day commercial paper at 4.90-5.00 percent against 5.00-5.10.

Sentiment in the bond market was cautious ahead of the finance ministry's T$35 billion seven-year bond auction on Friday, traders said. The markets will be closed on Tuesday for a domestic holiday and reopen on Wednesday. - J. Hu (5080815)
